.TH sysopctl 1 "October 2024" "v0.1.0" "System Management Script"
.SH NAME
sysopctl \- A script for managing system services, monitoring system load, and performing various administrative tasks.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sysopctl
.RI [ command ] [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B sysopctl
is a Bash script designed to assist in managing services, viewing system status, and performing system administration tasks. 

Commands include listing services, viewing system load, starting or stopping services, checking disk usage, monitoring processes, analyzing system logs, and performing backups.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI service\  list
List all running system services.
.TP
.BI service\  start\  <service>
Start a specified service.
.TP
.BI service\  stop\  <service>
Stop a specified service.
.TP
.BI system\  load
Display system load using
.B uptime.
.TP
.BI disk\  usage
Show disk usage of all mounted partitions using
.B df -h.
.TP
.BI process\  monitor
Monitor system processes using
.B htop.
.TP
.BI logs\  analyze
Analyze system logs using
.B journalctl.
.TP
.BI backup\  <path>
Backup specified files or directories to the current directory using
.B rsync.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display the script version.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Display help information and usage.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B sysopctl service list
List all running system services.
.TP
.B sysopctl system load
View the system load averages.
.TP
.B sysopctl service start nginx
Start the
.B nginx
service.
.TP
.B sysopctl disk usage
Display the current disk usage.
.TP
.B sysopctl process monitor
Open a real-time process monitor.
.TP
.B sysopctl logs analyze
Analyze the system's logs.
.TP
.B sysopctl backup /path/to/directory
Backup the specified directory to the current working directory.
.TP
.B sysopctl \-\-version
Display the script version information.

